task.summary: changed object property looping strategy for browser-compatibility
updated sinon.js in an attempt to fix issues in older browsers
added unit test for Animar's addAnimationToChain and integrated rewire which was necessary to make mocks
forgot to remove console logging from unit test (caused failure in early IE versions)
supporting files for bithound config addition
moved parameter validation function to helpers module
reformated helpers file for conditional exporting of developer-mode functions
removed ability to only pass in destination into add function
added defaults option to Animar constructor
added codecov.io reporting to travis config
removed codeclimate config and badges from readme and travis config
returned to es6 module exports for esdoc generation
Finished inital esdoc documentation. Removed hasAttribute and getModelFromAttribute from Element.
Moved webpack configurations to their own subfolder.
Changed Element & Attribute's render function to correctly order their transformation strings.
added prefixed transforms to Helper's setTransform method
changed codecov library in travis config.
added workaround for false test failure related to sinon's assert functionality.

Added lib artifacts to git
This is necessary to let people use the git repository directly as an npm module in order to test out an unstable build.
Decoupled the step rate from the frame rate.
Updated readme with more concrete example to give people something to work off of while I work on the full documentation
Cleaned up repo to prepare for the work to be done in the functional branch.
